@NODE Introduction
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    enqueueTorrent is a small commandline tool which helps to
    integrate MLdonkey support into your favourite Amiga
    Browser.

    enqueueTorrent forwards an URL (eDonkey links or torrents)
    via telnet from your Browser to MLdonkey, so you don't
    need to copy the URL and paste it manually with 'dllink'
    command into MLdonkey console. enqueueTorrent does exactly
    this for you. :-)

    It also has a small workaround for novasearch.net links
    which start with 'Http://' instead of 'http://' (MLdonkey
    does not accept the capital 'H' for some reason).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}


    - MorphOS 1.4 or AmigaOS 3.x
    - TCP/IP stack (bsdsocket.library v4 compatible)
    - running MLdonkey 2.5 or higher (localy or remotely)

    optional, but recommend:
    - MUI 3.x

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy enqueueTorrent drawer to a place you like.

    Information about integration of enqueueTorrent into the
    various browsers can be found in the following chapters.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Commandline
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À Commandline"


    @{b}CLI options@{ub}


    commandline template:
    URL/A,HOST,PORT/N,USER,PASS=PASSWORD,VERBOSE/S,SCR=PUBSCREEN



    @{b}Description@{ub}

    URL/A (required)

        The URL/link which should be added to MLdonkey down-
        load queue.

        ATTENTION: MLdonkey does only parse the URL for correct
        spelling. enqueueTorrent gets also an 'OK' when the
        torrent cannot be downloaded from MLdonkey, e.g. be-
        cause the server of this file is down.


    HOST (optional)

        The MLdonkey host. Internal default is 'localhost'.
        Only useful when you have MLdonkey running on another
        box and want to forward the URL via LAN/INET.


    PORT/N (optional)

        The MLdonkey telnet port. Internal default is '4000'.


    USER (optional)
    PASS=PASSWORD (optional)

        When MLdonkey is protected with user/ password or only
        password then you can use these options for auth-
        orisation.


    VERBOSE/S (optional)

        Prints out additional infos while processing. Only use-
        ful when somthing goes wrong and you want to know why.


    SCR=PUBSCREEN (optional, but highly recommend for browser
                   integration)

        Normaly enqueueTorrent prints out an error or an ok
        message to CON when it's done. You can redirect this
        message to a nice MUI requester on a certain public
        screen.

        Attention: screen names are case sensitive.

        When the screen is not available it will still output
        the message to CON. Using 'verbose' option at the same
        time turns of this info requester automatically.

        e.g.:

        enqueueTorrent http://foo.bar/some.torrent SCR Workbench

        - sends url http://foo.bar/1.torrent to MLdonkey and
          opens the info requester (ok or fail message) on
          Workbench Screen.

@ENDNODE


@NODE ibrowse
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À IBrowse"


    @{b}IBrowse@{ub}


    @{b}FAB Menu@{ub}
  
    Integrate enqueueTorrent into IBrowse Link popup menu, this works
    for torrent and donkey links. Just use right click on link and 
    choose "Send URL to MLdonkey..." after you've done the following 
    steps.


        - Open 'Preferences' -> 'Settings...', open page 'GUI' -> 
          'FAB Menus' then open the 'Link' branch in the listtree

        - Now drag from middle listview the 'Custom' entry to the 
          opened 'Link' branch in the right Listtree

        - Activate it and edit the settings. Set the Name to: 
          "Send URL to MLdonkey..."

        - Cycle the Action to 'Command' and choose the enqueueTorrent 
          binary as command

        - add '%l SCR %p' as arguments in the last stringgadget

        see also:   
    	@{" screenshot " link images/ibrowse_fabmenu.png/main  } (IBrowse, FAB Menu settings)
    


    @{b}MIME settings@{ub}

    Assign torrent filetype to enqueueTorrent. Attention: not all 
    servers are supporting application/x-bittorrent MIME type and the 
    torrent file will be shown as text in your browser window after 
    clicking the link. If that happens better use the popup menu. :-)        

        - Open 'Preferences' -> 'Settings...' and open page 'General' 
          ->  'MIME Types' 

        - press 'Add' and enter following information:

          MIME Type:     application / x-bittorrent

          Extension:     torrent

          Action:        external viewer
          
          Viewer:        dhx:path/to/enqueueTorrent 
          (just choose the enqueueTorrent executable from ASL-
          requester ;) )
 
          Arguments:     "%r" SCR %p
     
        see also:
        @{" screenshot " link images/ibrowse_mime.png/main     } (IBrowse, MIME settings)


    Don't forget to save your new settings! :-)

@ENDNODE


@NODE aweb
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À AWebII"


    @{b}AWebII@{ub}


    @{b}Popup Menu@{ub}
  
    Integrate enqueueTorrent into AWebs Link popup menu, this works
    for torrent and donkey links. Just use middle mouse (or ALT + 
    left mouse) on a link and choose "Send URL to MLdonkey..." after 
    you've done the following steps.

        - Open menu 'Settings' -> 'GUI settings', then choose
          'Popup' page and cycle 'Type' until you get 'Link
          popup menu' list.
       
        - Press 'Add' and add the following information for a new
          entry:

          Title:      Send URL to MLdonkey...

          Command:    SYSTEM dh0:path/to/enqueueTorrent "%u" SCR AWeb
          (replace the path with your path to the enqueueTorrent
          binary. When you have AWeb running on its own screen then
          use 'SCR Aweb' as shown above, when it's running on 
          Ambient then use 'SCR Workbench' and when it's running on
          some other public screen then use 'SCR <pubscreenname>'.)          
 
        see also:
        @{" screenshot " link images/aweb_popupmenu.png/main } (AWeb, Popup Menu settings)
     


    @{b}MIME settings@{ub}

    Assign torrent filetype to enqueueTorrent. Attention: not all 
    servers are supporting application/x-bittorrent MIME type and the 
    torrent file will be shown as text in your browser window after 
    clicking the link. If that happens better use the popup menu. :-)     

        - Open menu 'Settings' -> 'Browser settings', then choose
          'Viewers' page
       
        - Press 'Add' and add the following information for a new
          entry:

          Type:       APPLICATION / X-BITTORRENT
          
          Extension:  torrent

          Name:       dh0:path/to/enqueueTorrent
          (just use the ASL-requester to choose the enqueueTorrent
          executable ;) )

          Arguments:  "%u" SCR %n   

        see also:
        @{" screenshot " link images/aweb_mime.png/main      } (AWeb, MIME settings)


    Don't forget to save your new settings! :-)

@ENDNODE

@NODE voyager
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À Voyager"


    @{b}Voyager@{ub}


    @{b}Context Menu@{ub}
  
    Integrate enqueueTorrent into V's Link context menu, this works for 
    torrent and donkey links. Just use right click on link and choose
    "Send URL to MLdonkey..." after you've done the following steps.

        - Open menu 'Settings' -> 'General Settings', open 'Context 
          menu' page and cycle 'Type' until you've reached the 
          settings for the 'Link' context menu.

        - Press 'Add' and enter the following information for a new
          entry:

          Label:   Send URL to MLdonkey...
           
          Action:  AmigaDOS

          Now choose the enqueueTorrent executable with the ASL-
          requester and add the following arguments directly after the
          filename:

          "%l" SCR %p 

        see also:
        @{" screenshot " link images/v_contextmenu.png/main } (Voyager, Context Menu settings)

    
    Don't forget to save your new settings! :-)

@ENDNODE


@NODE FAQ
@TITLE "enqueueTorrent À FAQ"


    @{b}Frequently Asked Question@{ub}


    Q: I'm getting conection errors. What's wrong?

    A: Make sure MLdonkey is running and you've used correct host/ 
       port. As default enqueueTorrent uses localhost, port 4000 to
       communicate with MLdonkey.
    

@ENDNODE

